<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-30T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="1016" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1016">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/407a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-30T13:00:00-05:00">November 30, 1937—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>384. Press report under Tokyo date line November 29 states that it is
                            reported from Tientsin that the Peace Maintenance Commission there has
                            already reduced tariffs on a long list of articles imported from
                            Japan.</p>
                        <p>Please investigate and report promptly by naval radio.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>